║  STAGE 0: INPUT & QUALITY CONTROL                                 ║
├═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════┤
║                                                                   ║
║  Input: raw reads (FASTQ) OR consensus FASTA + metadata CSV       ║
║                                                                   ║
║  0a. If raw reads:   # this is obtional if given well good        ║
║      ├── Quality filter  → fastp / Nanofilt (remove low-Q reads)  ║
║      ├── Assembly        → IRMA (CDC, Ebola-optimised)            ║
║      │                     or SPAdes (general)                    ║
║      └── Consensus       → Generate consensus FASTA from assembly ║
║                                                                   ║
║  0b. consensus FASTA: # this is the main input format             ║
║      └── Validate format, check for N's, length                   ║
║                                                                   ║
║  0c. Quality metrics (both paths):                                ║
║      ├── Genome completeness (% vs expected length ~18,900 bp)    ║
║      ├── N-content (% ambiguous bases)                            ║
║      ├── Mean depth (if reads available)                          ║
║      ├── Genome quality flag: HIGH / MODERATE / LOW               ║
║      └── Missing regions (e.g., "3' terminal 285 bp")             ║
║                                                                   ║
║  Output: consensus FASTA + quality_metrics.json                   ║
║  Intelligence use: Report S1 (sample context), quality flag       ║
