║  STAGE 2: REFERENCE SELECTION & CONTEXT GATHERING                 ║
├═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════┤
║                                                                   ║
║  2a. Select reference genome                                      ║
║      ├── From reference_library/ebola/reference_genomes/          ║
║      │   (curated RefSeq accessions per species)                  ║
║      │   e.g., SUDV → NC_006432.1 (Boniface 1976)                ║
║      │        EBOV → NC_002549.1 (Mayinga 1976)                  ║
║      └── This is the coordinate system for all variant calling    ║
║                                                                   ║
║  2b. BLAST for context genomes                                    ║
║      ├── BLASTn against NCBI nt → top 50 hits                     ║
║      ├── Filter: same species, complete genomes, with dates       ║
║      └── These provide epidemiological context (closest outbreak) ║
║                                                                   ║
║  2c. Pull curated outbreak genomes                                ║
║      ├── From reference_library/ebola/outbreaks/outbreaks.csv     ║
║      │   (reference_genomes column has accessions)                ║
║      └── These are our trusted context set                        ║
║                                                                   ║
║  Output: reference_set = {ref_genome, blast_hits[], outbreak_refs[]}║
║  Intelligence use: Report S2 (closest reference, closest outbreak)║
