┌═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════┐
║  STAGE 3: GENOME ALIGNMENT & ANNOTATION                           ║
├═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════┤
║                                                                   ║
║  3a. Reference alignment (nucleotide)                             ║
║      ├── MAFFT (consensus FASTA vs reference genome)              ║
║      │   or minimap2 if long-read assembly with gaps              ║
║      └── Produces pairwise alignment → identifies all SNPs/indels ║
║                                                                   ║
║  3b. Genome annotation                                            ║
║      ├── Map gene boundaries from reference genome annotation     ║
║      │   (NP | VP35 | VP40 | GP | VP30 | VP24 | L)               ║
║      ├── For Ebola: gene order and boundaries are well-known      ║
║      │   NP:     1-3027     (470 aa after leader)                 ║
║      │   VP35:   3030-4407  (340 aa)                              ║
║      │   VP40:   4390-5384  (326 aa)                              ║
║      │   GP:     5459-7457  (676 aa precursor)                    ║
║      │   VP30:   7460-8309  (288 aa)                              ║
║      │   VP24:   8312-9070  (253 aa)                              ║
║      │   L:      9073-15711  (2212 aa)                            ║
║      │   (exact coordinates vary slightly by species/reference)   ║
║      └── Identify UTRs, intergenic regions, overlaps              ║
║                                                                   ║
║  3c. ORF prediction (validation)                                  ║
║      ├── Prodigal or MetaGeneAnnotator                            ║
║      └── Compare predicted ORFs to expected gene map —            ║
║          flag any missing/truncated genes                         ║
║                                                                   ║
║  Output: annotated_genome.gff3 + alignment_to_reference.bam       ║
║  Intelligence use: Report S2 (genes covered, missing regions)     ║
