┌═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════┐
║  STAGE 4: VARIANT CALLING (NUCLEOTIDE + AMINO ACID)               ║
├═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════┤
║                                                                   ║
║  4a. Nucleotide variant calling                                   ║
║      ├── From pairwise alignment (Stage 3a):                      ║
║      │   extract all SNPs, indels relative to reference           ║
║      ├── Tool: SNP-sites (from MSA) or BCFtools (from BAM)        ║
║      └── Output: VCF file with all nucleotide variants            ║
║                                                                   ║
║  4b. Protein extraction & translation                             ║
║      ├── Extract each ORF from annotated genome (Stage 3b)        ║
║      ├── Translate to amino acid sequence                         ║
║      └── 7 protein FASTAs: NP, VP35, VP40, GP, VP30, VP24, L     ║
║                                                                   ║
║  4c. Protein alignment                                            ║
║      ├── MAFFT: each protein vs reference amino acid sequence     ║
║      └── 7 pairwise protein alignments                            ║
║                                                                   ║
║  4d. Amino acid variant calling                                   ║
║      ├── From each protein alignment: extract AA substitutions    ║
║      ├── Generate HGVS notation: e.g., GP:A82V, VP35:T230A       ║
║      ├── Classify: synonymous / non-synonymous / nonsense         ║
║      └── Map each variant to gene_function domain (e.g.,          ║
║          "GP:A82V is in RBD aa 54-201")                           ║
║                                                                   ║
║  4e. Negative findings check                                      ║
║      ├── Cross-reference against genotype_phenotype_associations  ║
║      │   for known concerning mutations                           ║
║      ├── Check: are known concerning variants ABSENT?             ║
║      │   e.g., GP:N439K — NOT detected ✓                        ║
║      │        VP35:R312A — NOT detected ✓                       ║
║      └── Report negative findings explicitly                      ║
║                                                                   ║
║  Output: variants.json {nt_variants[], aa_variants[],             ║
║          negative_findings[], domain_context[]}                   ║
║  Intelligence use: Report S3 (all mutations + domain context +    ║
║                    negative findings) — THE CORE OUTPUT           ║
